# Systemic_Analysis_and_Vulnerability_Index (SAVI)

## Repository Description
A conceptual mathematical framework designed to model, track, and analyze structural failures, historical socioeconomic gaps, institutional biases, and educational deficits that correlate with systemic vulnerabilities and mass incarceration. This protocol aims to leverage logic-based modeling to shift public discourse from purely reactive punitive measures toward root-cause identification and proactive policy reform.

---

## Architectural Framework

This model maps complex sociological data into multi-dimensional state vectors to evaluate institutional accountability.

### 1. Vector Quantization Matrix

Let $V$ represent the systemic vulnerability vector, defined across key institutional pillars:

$$V = \begin{bmatrix} E_{edu} \\ M_{med} \\ L_{leg} \\ S_{eco} \end{bmatrix}$$

Where:
* $E_{edu}$: The Education Index (proactive risk prevention vs. complete systemic neglect).
* $M_{med}$: The Media Influence Filter (unregulated predatory manipulation vs. ethical accountability).
* $L_{leg}$: The Legal Disparity Matrix (punitive mass incarceration vs. rehabilitative protection).
* $S_{eco}$: The Socioeconomic Metric (capital extraction vs. community stabilization).

